    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - MOUNTING ENGINE ON STAND -
        Mounting Engine On Stand
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Mounting Engine On Stand</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="mount" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Mounting Engine On Stand</title>
            <figure id="f1200101" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2620.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Location of Coolant Drain Plugs</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right Coolant Drain Plug</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Level Gauge</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left Coolant Drain Plug</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Cooler/Filter Header</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the coolant from the crankcase by removing two coolant drain plugs. There is one
                    drain plug on each side of the engine, at the rear of the crankcase behind the exhaust manifolds.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200102" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3256.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Location of Oil Drain Plug</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Pan</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Drain Plug</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil drain plug. Allow the oil to drain from the oil pan into a suitable
                    container.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200103" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3307.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Oil Level Gauge</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Level Gauge</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Stud Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the stud nut that secures the slotted oil level gauge mountiong bracket to the
                    right exhaust manifold. Remove the oil level gauge.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After all fluids are drained from the engine, install the plugs. Tighten the oil drain
                    plug to the special torque value.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possibly death, attach the hoist hook lifting bracket at
                        the engine lifting eyes before lifting the engine. Failure to do so can cause the engine to lift
                        on one end and swing out, injuring any personnel standing in the area.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the hoist hook lifting bracket at the engine lifting eyes. Use a safety catch on
                    the hoist hook when lifting the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possibly death, or engine damage, use only grade 8 or
                        greater metric bolts when mounting the engine to the stand. Other bolts may sheer, causing the
                        engine to fall from the engine stand.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For specific directions on the safe use of engine mounting stands and adapter plates, refer to
                        the manufacturer's instructions included with these parts.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>Use the correct engine stand adapter plate when mounting the engine to the stand.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1200104" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3174.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Engine Stand Adapter Plate to Engine</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Mounting Adapter Plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Spacer</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mountiong Bolts (3)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position and secure the engine stand mounting adapter plate to the right side of the
                    engine. Use three grade 8 bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the engine to the stand using the specified adapter plate and grade 8 or greater
                    mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
